# Shared project memory

Always consult the `.cursor-memory` directory for:

- **Architecture**: `.cursor-memory/architecture/` — system patterns, API design, infra decisions
- **Conventions**: `.cursor-memory/conventions/` — coding standards, naming, git workflow
- **Decisions**: `.cursor-memory/decisions/` — ADRs and prior decisions
- **Snippets**: `.cursor-memory/snippets/` — reusable code (auth, db, ui)
- **Playbooks**: `.cursor-memory/playbooks/` — debugging, deployment, onboarding

Treat `.cursor-memory` as the shared project memory. Prefer patterns and decisions defined there when they apply. Use `memory-index.md` as the entry point.
